data.chText: 叮当（或铿锵）作响；使叮当（或铿锵）作响
data.enText: to make a loud ringing sound like that of metal being hit; to cause sth to make this sound

data.chText: 塔楼上的钟当当地敲响了。
data.enText: Bells were clanging in the tower.

data.chText: 有轨电车哐啷哐啷沿街驶过。
data.enText: The trams clanged their way along the streets.

example: he could hear the clang of distant bells

value.def: When a large metal object clangs, it makes a loud noise.

example.ex: A little later the church bell clanged...
example.tran: 过了一小会儿，教堂的钟当当敲响了。

example.ex: The door clanged shut behind them.
example.tran: 门在他身后咣的一声关上了。

example.ex: He pulled the gates to with a clang...
example.tran: 他把大门咣当一声带上了。

example.ex: In the older part of the city, the clang and bang of the builders goes on all day.
example.tran: 在老城区，建筑工人的咣咣当当声每天不绝于耳。

value.tran: 发出嘡啷声(或叮当声);叮当作响
